  <h1 class="gd-h1">When Is the Best Time to Go Heliskiing?</h1>
  <p class="gd-byline" style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:12.5px;letter-spacing:.05em;color:var(--blue-soft);opacity:.9;margin:16px 0 0">By <a href="/about" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:3px">Vegard Knudsen</a> · Founder, Heliski Travel · Updated 29 Jun 2026</p>
  <p class="gd-lede">The best time to go heliskiing depends entirely on where you go. Somewhere in the world it is heliski season in almost every month, from midwinter powder in Canada and Japan to spring descents in Iceland and Norway and a summer window in New Zealand. This guide maps the whole calendar so you can time your trip, then explore <a href="/packages">the packages</a> and <a href="/iceland">Iceland</a>.</p>
</div></section>
